            observations: '',
            objectives: 'A movement to push the cloud towards the edges of the networks is ongoing. Big, remote, energy-hungry datacenters will continue to exist but new distributed clouds are appearing in shared infrastructures, research labs, universities, condominiums and communities in general, giving raise to edge clouds and fog computing. This work aims at design a new distributed and decentralized architecture for VM/container (e.g., OpenStack, LXC, Docker) scheduling on edge clouds where nodes in the same vicinity collaborate locally to discover, manage and allocate resources without the need for remote centralized nodes, and are also able to exchange resources with near-by vicinities managing other sets of nodes close-by. Specific challenges include extending schedulers to be able to cooperate in decentralized manner and to schedule jobs comprising multiple tasks according to heuristics that distribute load and minimize service latency and job makespan.',
            status: 'Assigned',
