            location: 'INESC-ID',
            courses: 'MERC, MEIC-A, MEIC-T',
            observations: 'Este trabalho já se encontra pré-atribuído ao aluno João Tiago.',
            objectives: 'The InterPlanetary File System (IPFS) is a hypermedia distribution protocol, addressed by content and identities. IPFS enables the creation of completely distributed applications. Currently, IPFS has not no notion of block popularity. A node that fetches a block will have it cached until garbage collected. A node won’t serve a block it unless it fetched it itself before and stored it. This work aims at extending IPFS with intelligent caching and hoarding capabilities that can serve as the basis for making popular content more available through, e.g., a Content Delivery Network (CDN). Specific challenges including determining when a block is considered hot and where it should be stored to improve IPFS availability and performance.',
            status: 'Assigned',
