            objectives: 'The goals of this thesis is to develop &quot;agents&quot; (NPCs)  that will play in the multi-player game designed to help children victims of cyberbullying.\n\nThe game features situations of cyberbullying, and each player may be confronted with a direct request for help from a victim, a personal message from a bystander inquiring what they should do in the situation, an order from a bystander to take action (negative or pro-social behavior).  Some of the bystanders in the game will be NPCs (agents) that will act according to their own personality. \n\nThe game features different scenarios and each one, the number of bystanders that do nothing, place a like or post a comment increases, as the incident progresses throughout time, is manipulated, and as such, the agents that play the game have to be prepared for situations where there are several agents in the situation.\n',
