            observations: 'http://www.math.ist.utl.pt/~padao/teaching/thesis1718/',
            objectives: 'IoT devices are populating our world from watches, to cars, to light bulbs, and fridges. Given the low computation capabilities of some of these devices, and the lack of standards, everytime a new IoT device is added to a network, one is adding a possible entry point for an attacker.\n\nIn this work we want to analyse the security of IoT devices (and consequently home networks) in particular by exploiting its APIs. (black-box testing)\n\n1. Study existing methodologies for testing APIs.\n2. Extraction of the execution models of such devices according to the outputs.\n3. Analisys of the security of such models.',
