            observations: 'For more information about this proposal, get in touch with the proponent of this work (nuno.santos@inesc-id.pt).',
            objectives: 'With the proliferation of smartphones, public transportation is progressively shifting towards the adoption of mobile ticketing applications in order to complement or even replace traditional ticketing solutions. However, unless properly engineered, mobile ticketing applications are prone to a new class of vulnerabilities allowing for fraudulent attacks and copied digital tickets.\n\nThe goal of this project will be to study, develop, and evaluate security solutions for a real-world mobile ticketing application. To this end, the first step will be to analyze the security protocols, the design and implementation of the target application, which has been developed for commodity Android devices. As a result of this analysis, improvements and fixes must be proposed and implemented. The second step will be to develop and evaluate a security solution for the target application based on ARM TrustZone technology. By leveraging this technology, it will be possible to make the application robust against attacks that can subvert the Android OS entirely.',
            status: 'Assigned',
            requirements: 'The candidate must be highly motivated to work at the low levels of abstraction (e.g., if necessary, work on binary code reverse engineering). It&#39;s highly advised to have background courses on computer security and mobile computing.',
