            objectives: 'Web applications are a critical piece in today&#39;s digital world. Compromising these might lead to the exploitation of backend systems and the leak of sensitive information that should not be exposed to the public. \n\nThe goal of these thesis is to perform the study of existing tools and propose a methodology that, with the help of programmers, would simplify the testing of web-applications.\n\n1. Survey the tools and methodologies to study security of web applications.\n2. Propose a language of annotations that would mark entry, evaluation, and exit nodes of the execution graph.\n3. Perform the analysis of these execution flows and return possible explotation inputs.',
